Oxea I (
Figure 3C
) abundant, stout, straight and curved, smooth with hastate ends: 500–788.8–1060 /20–34.6– 50 µm (length/ thickness).

Oxea II (
Figure 3D
) smooth, slender, straight to slightly curved with acerate ends: 146.3–267.5–417.6 / 5.3– 8.1–10.6 µm (length/ thickness).

Styles (
Figure 3E
) less abundant than oxeas, smooth, straight, with regular blunt and pointed ends: 205.2– 587.7–913.1 / 20.5–30.5–41 µm (length/ thickness).
